The whole point of CS is to push Pakistani music and experiment with different sounds. In a lot of the harder, rock oriented songs you see people whining the most. Really refreshing.

snippet.textDisplay:
*Coke studio needs Rohail Hyatt badly "OR" these guys are gonna drive it down the valley* This is not rock, this is pure torture. It's QB who's selling the song. And I got nothing against the dude who sang first, he's probably a very fine singer, but it's just the garbage he's thrown into make him look stinky as well. 

For everyone complaining that one needs to know *ROCK GENRE* to like this song, *GIVE ME A FUCKIN BREAK*. 
Remember *'Ob-La-Di, Ob-La-Da'* songh by the Beatles, it was a ROCK song as well and probably the worst one ever. If Beatles can produce bad rock than how is Strings immune to it? Having a taste in rock doesn't mean everything out of it has to be good. A bunch of fuckin *"LOOK HOW WHITE I AM"* douches barking about the rock for no apparent reason. The first 3 minutes of the song are total GIBBERISH.﻿
